// Suite   : syntax_include
// Feature : nested .include chain resolved via `-I lib`  (a → b → c)
// Verifies:
//   - `-I` include search path resolves the top-level include
//   - parent-file-relative resolution still works for nested includes
//     once the first one has been located via `-I`
//   - declarations and rules from all depths are visible after merge
//   - .output directives in included files are honoured
//
// Graph (edges)
//   1 → 2 → 3 → 1   (a cycle: all three nodes can reach themselves)
//   4 → 5            (a tail: neither node is in a cycle)
